               <p>1288. <persName id="def1-1288-18440408" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-1288-18440408" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1288-18440408" type="surname" value="BROCKLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1288-18440408" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JOHN BROCKLEY</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18440408-1288-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18440408-1288-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18440408-1288-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp> for stealing 3/4 lb. of soap, value 3<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18440408-name-1401" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1401" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1401" type="surname" value="MATTHEWS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1401" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18440408-1288-offence-1 t18440408-name-1401"></join>John Matthews</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1402" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1402" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1402" type="surname" value="WHITE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1402" type="given" value="VOLTAIRE"></interp>VOLTAIRE WHITE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am sixteen yean old, and am in the service of Mr. John Matthews—he keeps a tallow-chandler's shop in King-street, Hammer<lb></lb>smith. On the evening of the 18th of March I went on an errand, and on my return, I stopped for a minute at my master's window—I saw the prisoner in the shop—I saw him take a piece of soap from the box, and put it into his right-hand coat-pocket—I went into the shop, and stood as a customer—my mistress came in, and the prisoner told her to serve me first—she said, "He does not want serving—he is my own boy."—I said, "He has taken a piece of soap"—he took it from hit pocket, and said, "Weigh it, I meant to pay for it."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did not he go out of the shop after you went for the policeman? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, and went over the Suspension-bridge—we went round to his house—he was not taken at his house, but on the other side of the bridge—the scale is very near the box of soap—I swear that it was not out of the scale that he took the soap—I don't know that my master had a quarrel with the prisoner, about a man be had turned out—I have not noticed him to deal at the shop before—I have been there five months—he made an attempt to get away—I believe he was coming towards the policeman, and he has been on bail ever since.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Could you tell whether, when the prisoner had the soap in his hand, before he put it in his pocket, he could see you, or was aware that he Was observed? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> He did not notice me till I was about to enter the shop—he had put it partly into his pocket before I entered, and when I entered, he pushed it in in a more flurried manner—I did not examine the pocket—I do not know whether it would require any. force to get it in.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1403" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1403" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1403" type="surname" value="MATTHEWS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1403" type="given" value="AMY"></interp>AMY MATTHEWS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am wife of John Matthews. I left the shop on the 18th of March, for a short time, and on my return I saw the prisoner and my lad in the shop—the prisoner said, "Serve him first"—I said, "He does not require serving, he is my own boy"—my boy then said, "Take that piece of soap out of your pocket directly, sir "—the prisoner took it out, and said,</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184404080215"></xptr>
               <p>"Weigh it, I intend to pay for it"—I am rare he took it out of hit right-hand coat-pocket, and he handed it to me—I said, "If you intended to pay for it, why did you put it in your pocket?"—he said" Don't make a fuss about it, weigh it, and I will pay you for it"—I placed it on one side—I told the boy to fetch a policeman, and the prisoner followed the boy shortly after—this is the piece of soap—it is common white soap—I know it by these holes in it, which I had noticed.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Had you a good many pieces of soap in that box? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—it is an inferior kind, but there was no better in that box.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1404" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1404" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1404" type="surname" value="GRAY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1404" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM GRAY</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable T</hi> 195.) I found the prisoner, over Hammersmith Suspension-bridge, at near seven o'clock that evening—I told him he must go with me to the station—he said, "For what?"—I said, "Con<lb></lb>cerning stealing a piece of soap"—he said, "I suppose it is concerning the soap the man gave me"—I found nothing but 7 3/4 <hi rend="italic">d</hi>. on him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Where did he live? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> In Queen-street, Hammer-smith—he was coining towards his own house, from the opposite side of the water—he surrendered here on Saturday.</p>
               <p>
